HEADWORD: Prosody
<hw>Pros"o*dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>prosodia</ets> the tone or accent of a syllable, Gr. <?/ a song
sung to, or with, an accompanying song, the accent accompanying the
pronunciation; <?/ to + <?/ song, ode: cf. F. <ets>prosodie</ets>. See
<er>Ode</er>.]</ety> <def>That part of grammar which treats of the
quantity of syllables, of accent, and of the laws of versification or
metrical composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

